Abstract: This paper presents the results of an exploratory survey of the applicability of discriminant analysis to the determination of the medium-term (two-year) exchange rate changes. Using a discriminant function developed on observations drawn from 1961&ndash;1964 and 1965&ndash;1968, the authors have correctly predicted the devaluation or nondevaluation of 86 percent of the countries tested for the period 1971&ndash;1972. These results indicate predictive power at the .001 level of significance. A reduction of 36 percent in classification error is achieved by the method.&copy; 1975 JIBS. Journal of International Business Studies (1975) 6, 33&ndash;50
